div.div:
(1) As is usually the case with React apps, the actual JSX can be in the form of stateless components.
(2) The "store" is direct memory representation of what is visible on screen. Every variable in it is wired directly to some value on screen. If not, it is a logic/business concern and should be a part of the "engine" state, not the UI.
(3) An application engine can drive the UI by calling API functions that manipulate the store, thereby manipulating what's on screen.
